message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation using deep learning techniques. The use of Bayesian deep learning and uncertainty estimation also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the focus on medical imaging and the specific pathologies studied suggest that it could also belong to the medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests that it could also belong to the neural networks (cs.NEURON) sub-category.
